---
import PageLayout from "../../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="You define yourself"
  description="Epistemological authority and defining your own experiences — NDMDs Neurodiversity in Medicine Society."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
    <header class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-teal/80">
        <a class="underline decoration-brand-cyan underline-offset-2 hover:decoration-brand-teal" href="/about/"
          >About</a
        >
        <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
        <span class="text-brand-teal">You define yourself</span>
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-extrabold text-brand-teal sm:text-5xl">
        You define yourself
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-teal/90">
        Labels and diagnoses can open doors — but they can also shrink people into boxes
        drawn by someone else. NDMDs is not here to test you or gatekeep who “counts” as
        neurodivergent. We care about how <em>you</em> experience your mind, your senses,
        and your place in medicine — because that knowledge belongs to you first.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-12 max-w-3xl space-y-10">
      <blockquote
        class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-brand-cyan bg-brand-surface/80 px-5 py-5 text-lg italic text-brand-teal/95"
      >
        <p>
          In academic literature, the power to define a group and its members is called{" "}
          <cite class="font-semibold not-italic">epistemological authority</cite>. The
          neurodivergent community has often had to fight to retain it, when diagnosis is
          expensive, slow, and framed around deficit. Here, you define your own
          experiences — we are peers, not gatekeepers.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote
        class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-brand-teal/40 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-lime/20 to-brand-cyan/15 px-5 py-5 text-lg italic text-brand-teal/95"
      >
        <p>
          You define your own experiences. How you sense your surroundings, how you
          interact with the world, how you are in this moment. That definition is
          something that can never be written by anyone but you.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-lg text-brand-teal/90">
        Take a breath when you need one. However you show up in tutorials, on placement,
        or in quiet moments alone — your perspective is yours to name. We are glad you
        are here.
      </p>
    </div>

    <nav class="mt-14 flex flex-wrap gap-3 border-t border-brand-teal/10 pt-10" aria-label="About section">
      <a
        href="/about/neurodiversity/"
        class="inline-flex rounded-full border-2 border-brand-teal/25 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-brand-teal transition hover:border-brand-teal/40"
        >What is neurodiversity?</a
      >
      <a
        href="/about/mythbusting/"
        class="inline-flex rounded-full border-2 border-brand-teal/25 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-brand-teal transition hover:border-brand-teal/40"
        >Mythbusting</a
      >
      <a
        href="/about/"
        class="inline-flex rounded-full bg-brand-teal px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-brand-teal-muted"
        >Back to About us</a
      >
    </nav>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
